courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, B2, C1, C2, D1, D2, D3, D4, D5, and F. C4, D5, and F should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). NOTE: Areas C3, C4, and F may be fulfilled in concentration courses. Refer to online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP) and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR). USCP requirement can be satisfied by some (but not all) courses within GE categories: C3, C4, D1, D3, D4, D5, or F. USCP may also be fulfilled in concentration.
